                    <h2 class="text-gray-800 text-xl font-semibold text-center mb-1">Alternate Nostril Breathing</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm text-center">This breathing technique can quickly calm the mind and body, and reduce anxiety and stress.</p>
                </div>
    
                <!-- Pose 4: Humming Bee Breath -->
                <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-lg transition-transform transform hover:scale-105">
                    <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRhAYCUaRYxzmZdMV3J9MipZC3fzdjKVZje107177TElvXESDA2co7iBOLJI4xflizFAnw&usqp=CAU" alt="Humming Bee Breath" class="mb-2 mx-auto rounded-md h-32 object-cover">
                    <h2 class="text-gray-800 text-xl font-semibold text-center mb-1">Humming Bee Breath</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm text-center">Humming Bee Breath is effective at releasing built-up tension in the body.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <!-- Relaxation Videos & Audios -->
        <div class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 p-8 w-full shadow-md min-h-64">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Relaxation Videos & Audios</h2>
            <p class="p-4">Engage with calming audio or visual resources to help soothe your mind and alleviate PTSD symptoms.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                <li class="pb-3"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eiB-ibIwJN4" class="text-blue-700 underline" target="_blank">10-Minute Guided Meditation</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y8jj12DnAys" class="text-blue-700 underline" target="_blank">Relaxing Nature Sounds</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    
        
        <!-- FAQs Section -->
        <div id="faqs" class="faq-section bg-gray-50 shadow-md p-6 w-full rounded-lg">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    
            <!-- FAQ 1 -->
            <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-gray-300">
                <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-gray-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800">Who is at risk for developing PTSD?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-arrow text-gray-700">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                    <p>While anyone can develop PTSD after experiencing a traumatic event, certain factors may increase the risk. These include the severity and duration of the trauma, personal history of mental health issues, a lack of social support, and a history of substance abuse. Additionally, individuals who have experienced previous traumas may be at greater risk for developing PTSD after subsequent traumatic events. It's also worth noting that some populations, such as military veterans, first responders, and survivors of violent crime, may face higher rates of PTSD due to the nature of their experiences.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
    
            <!-- FAQ 2 -->
            <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-gray-300">
                <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-gray-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800">How is PTSD diagnosed?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-arrow text-gray-700">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                    <p>A diagnosis of PTSD is typically made by a mental health professional through a comprehensive evaluation. This process may include a clinical interview, a discussion of the individual's history and symptoms, and the use of standardized assessment tools. To be diagnosed with PTSD, the individual must meet specific criteria outlined in the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM-5). These criteria include experiencing a traumatic event, exhibiting certain symptoms for at least one month, and demonstrating significant distress or impairment in social, occupational, or other important areas of functioning. Early diagnosis and intervention are crucial for effective treatment.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
    
            <!-- FAQ 3 -->
            <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-gray-300">
                <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-gray-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800">Can children develop PTSD?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-arrow text-gray-700">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                    <p>Yes, children can develop PTSD after experiencing or witnessing traumatic events. The symptoms in children may manifest differently than in adults, often showing through behavioral changes rather than verbal expressions of distress. Children may experience nightmares, exhibit clinginess, show regression in developmental milestones, or have difficulty concentrating. It is essential for caregivers and educators to recognize signs of distress in children and provide appropriate support. Early intervention through counseling or play therapy can be particularly effective in helping children process trauma and develop coping skills.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
    
            <!-- FAQ 4 -->
            <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-gray-300">
                <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-gray-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800">What should someone do if they think they have PTSD?</h3>
                    <span class="faq-arrow text-gray-700">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                    <p>If someone suspects they have PTSD, the first step is to seek professional help. This can involve reaching out to a mental health professional, such as a psychologist or psychiatrist, who specializes in trauma-related disorders. They can provide a thorough assessment and recommend appropriate treatment options. It's also helpful to connect with support groups or communities where individuals can share their experiences and coping strategies. Recognizing and acknowledging the symptoms is a significant step towards recovery, and seeking help is a sign of strength, not weakness.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- extra -->
    </div>
</div>
<script>
    // Function to toggle FAQ visibility
function toggleFAQ(element) {
    const answer = element.nextElementSibling;
    answer.classList.toggle('hidden'); // Toggle visibility
    const arrow = element.querySelector('.faq-arrow');
    arrow.textContent = answer.classList.contains('hidden') ? '▼' : '▲'; // Change arrow direction
}

// Start breathing exercise
document.getElementById('try-breathing-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
    const exerciseCard = document.getElementById('exerciseCard');
    exerciseCard.classList.remove('hidden');

    let timeLeft = 120; // Total duration of the exercise in seconds
    const timerDisplay = document.getElementById('timer');
    const instruction = document.getElementById('instruction');
    const breathingDuration = 4; // Seconds for inhale/exhale
    let inhale = true;

    timerDisplay.textContent = timeLeft;

    // Update breathing every second
    const countdown = setInterval(function() {
        timeLeft--;
        timerDisplay.textContent = timeLeft;

        if (timeLeft % 8 === 0) { // Every 8 seconds (4s inhale + 4s exhale)
            instruction.textContent = inhale ? "Inhale" : "Exhale";
            inhale = !inhale; // Toggle inhale/exhale
        }

        if (timeLeft <= 0) {
            clearInterval(countdown);
            instruction.textContent = "Great job! You're done!";
            document.getElementById('animation-circle').classList.add('hidden'); // Optionally hide circle at the end
        }
    }, 1000);
});

// Close breathing exercise
document.getElementById('closeExercise').addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.getElementById('exerciseCard').classList.add('hidden');
    clearInterval(countdown); // Clear the interval when closing
});

// Event listener for the FAQs button
document.getElementById('view-faqs-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
    const faqsSection = document.getElementById('faqs'); // Get the FAQs section
    
    // Scroll to the FAQs section smoothly
    faqsSection.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
});
// for horizontal scroll
const carousel = document.getElementById('carousel');
const leftButton = document.getElementById('leftButton');
const rightButton = document.getElementById('rightButton');

let scrollAmount = 0;

rightButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
    scrollAmount += carousel.clientWidth * 0.6;
    carousel.scrollTo({
        left: scrollAmount,
        behavior: 'smooth'
    });
});

leftButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
    scrollAmount -= carousel.clientWidth * 0.6;
    carousel.scrollTo({
        left: scrollAmount,
        behavior: 'smooth'
    });
});
</script>